'''Balgha''' ({{lang-ary|البلغة|l-bəlġa}}), also spelled '''balga''', '''belgha''', or '''belga''', are heelless [[slipper]]s made from [[leather]]. They are part of traditional dress in the [[Maghreb]].

Balgha are worn by men and women of all social classes, both in urban and rural areas.

