In [[Europe]], Spanish is an official language of Spain, the country after which it is named and from which it originated. It is widely spoken in [[Gibraltar]], and also commonly spoken in [[Andorra]], although [[Catalan language|Catalan]] is the official language there.<ref>{{cite web
