Spanish is also spoken by small communities in other European countries, such as the [[United Kingdom]], [[France]], [[Italy]], and [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/languages/european_languages/languages/spanish.shtml |title=BBC Education — Languages Across Europe — Spanish |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date= |accessdate=20 August 2012}}</ref> Spanish is an official language of the [[European Union]]. In [[Switzerland]], which had a massive influx of Spanish migrants in the 20th century, Spanish is the [[first language|native language]] of 2.2% of the population.<ref>{{cite web
